- Top-performing models refer to those with the highest recent evaluation metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall, and F1 score; 
- Model performance metrics are key indicators of a model's effectiveness in making predictions; 
- Access logs are records of when and how users interact with the models, such as viewing or downloading predictions.

sql:
SELECT model_name
FROM models
ORDER BY model_name;

SELECT model_id, model_name
FROM models
ORDER BY model_id;

SELECT model_name
FROM models
ORDER BY model_name ASC;
